_Further Reading_

* Tanenbaum, Andrew S. and David J. Wetherall. 2010. **Computer Networks**, 5th edition. Prentice Hall. This book actually covers all of the layers of the Internet, with a new addition of a section on network and application security. This book is not overly technical, but still covers technical concepts, like the three-way handshake for TCP connections. Wetherall is the instructor for Coursera's Computer Networking course.
* Bonaventure O, **Computer Networking: Principles, Protocol, and Practice**  
[http://www.saylor.org/site/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/Computer-Networking-Principles-Bonaventure-1-30-31-OTC1.pdf](http://www.saylor.org/site/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/Computer-Networking-Principles-Bonaventure-1-30-31-OTC1.pdf) This is a free open source text book covering theory of networks.  
It is the course text of the [http://www.saylor.org/courses/cs402/](http://www.saylor.org/courses/cs402/) Computer Communications and Networks free on-line course
* Masha du Toit, Anna Malczyk and Jean-Paul van Belle, **Internet Super User Text Book**, GetSmarter Publishing Jan 2010  
[http://www.internetsuperuser.com/download-the-internet-super-user-textbook](http://www.internetsuperuser.com/download-the-internet-super-user-textbook) South African text book used in their complementary course. It is a complete reference about the workings and use of the Internet. Registration required for download.

* "History of the internet" is an animated documentary explaining the inventions from time-sharing to filesharing, from Arpanet to Internet. The clip was made by Melih Bilgil — http://www.lonja.de
The history is told using the PICOL icons, which are available on picol.org. You can get news about this project on blog.picol.org .

Voice-over by Steve Taylor http://voice-pool.com
You can get more information on this movie on my website
http://www.lonja.de/motion/mo_history...
or on the PICOL-Project site where you can download a pre-release of the icons.
http://blog.picol.org/

If you are interested in more Internet history you can also read/watch:
- ISOC: History of the internet: http://www.isoc.org/internet/history/
- http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_...
- Geschichte des Internet (german & link to Amazon): http://tinyurl.com/4kzlwq
- Computer Networks: The Heralds Of Resource Sharing http://tinyurl.com/apocod

